    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nAt the page, https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/wiki/UI-Customization#borders:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n-- LSP settings (for overriding per client)\r\nlocal handlers =  {\r\n  [\"textDocument/hover\"] =  vim.lsp.with(vim.lsp.handlers.hover, {border = border}),\r\n  [\"textDocument/signatureHelp\"] =  vim.lsp.with(vim.lsp.handlers.signature_help, {border = border }),\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut this causes an error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n îª‡  Error  16:28:15 msg_show.lua_error Error executing vim.schedule lua callback: /usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:1697: 'width' key must be a positive Integer\r\nstack traceback:\r\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_open_win'\r\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:1697: in function 'handler'\r\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:574: in function ''\r\n\tvim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo fix it I have to hard-code the `height` and `width` for both:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n{border = border, width=10, height=10}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo it seems that someone made a change that either validating/removing the default `height`&`width` when it is not set!",
    "closed_at": "2024-02-28T08:59:30Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Nevermind! I just realized this is caused by the fact that if noice.nvim is used and you have its config like this;\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nrequire('noice').setup {\r\n  lsp = {\r\n    -- override markdown rendering so that **cmp** and other plugins use **Treesitter**\r\n    override = {\r\n      ['vim.lsp.util.convert_input_to_markdown_lines'] = true,\r\n      ['vim.lsp.util.stylize_markdown'] = true,\r\n      ['cmp.entry.get_documentation'] = true,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n  presets = {\r\n    lsp_doc_border = true,\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nthen you will **have to** give up using built-in `vim.lsp.buf.hover`, and use its `require(\"noice.lsp\").hover()` instead.\r\n\r\nReference: https://github.com/folke/noice.nvim/issues/258.",
