            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for your comment https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3036#issuecomment-1968518789, @nyngwang! This was driving me nuts. ;-)\r\n\r\nReplacing `vim.lsp.buf.hover()` with `require(\"noice.lsp\").hover()` also solved my problem where, when using noice, the LSP's floating window was not using a border even though I tried things like:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n[\"textDocument/hover\"] =  vim.lsp.with(vim.lsp.handlers.hover, {border = \"rounded\"})\r\n```\r\n",
